table in html 
Tables in html
The <table> tag is used to define tables in html .It is used to format and display tabular data.

Tags in Table
tr tag:
used to display table Row

td tag:
used to diplay the table data

th tag:
used in place of table data for displaying table headers

Example :-
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<style>
table, th, td {
  border:1px solid black;
}
</style>
<body>
 <h2>A basic HTML table</h2>
 <table>
  <tr>
    <th>Company</th>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Country</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>GFG</td>
    <td>Yash</td>
    <td>Germany</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>De shaw</td>
    <td>Pragati</td>
    <td>Mexico</td>
  </tr>
</table>
 </body>
</html>


Output




Screenshot-(3)




Note:-
we can define as many as table rows as we want.



To add a caption to the table ,we use <caption> tag inside table .

thead tag :
used to wrap table head(caption and tr with th)

tbody tag:
used to wrap the table body.



Colspan attribute
This attribute is used to create cells spanning multiple columns

<th colspan="3"> Harry </th>

EXAMPLE
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
table, th, td {
  border: 1px solid black;
  border-collapse: collapse;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
 <table style="width:100%">
  <tr>
    <th colspan="2">Name</th>
    <th>Age</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Ram</td>
    <td>Sharma</td>
    <td>43</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Eve</td>
    <td>Jackson</td>
    <td>59</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>



Output


Screenshot-(4)

Rowspan Attribute
The value of the rowspan attribute represents the number of rows to span.

EXAMPLE
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
table, th, td {
  border: 1px solid black;
  border-collapse: collapse;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
 <table style="width:100%">
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <td>Raju</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <th rowspan="2">Number</th>
    <td>9999</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>555</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>


Output
Screenshot-(6)






